-- Mozambique Province Wants Limestone Mine Investors, Diario Says
-- B y   F r e d   K a t e r e r e
-- 2012-01-03T12:47:13Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-01-03/mozambique-province-wants-limestone-mine-investors-diario-says.html
     Jan. 3 (Bloomberg) ---  Mozambique ’s Zambezia province is
looking for investors to mine limestone in two districts that
have deposits estimated at almost 200 million metric tons,
 Diario de Mocambique  reported, citing the province’s development
plan for 2011-2020.  Authorities are also seeking investors to build a cement
plant in the province, the Beira-based newspaper reported.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Fred Katerere in Maputo at 
 fkaterere@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net  